# Force LF line endings for all source and config files so Windows
# checkouts don't introduce CRLF that breaks gofumpt / golangci-lint /
# any other tool that asserts byte-identical output. Without this,
# `make fmt-check` fails on Windows CI runners because they default to
# `core.autocrlf=true`, which silently converts LF to CRLF on checkout.

# Treat as text + normalise to LF on commit + check out with LF.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Explicit overrides for binary types — Git would usually detect these,
# but pinning makes the intent clear.
*.png    binary
*.jpg    binary
*.jpeg   binary
*.gif    binary
*.ico    binary
*.zip    binary
*.tar.gz binary
*.gz     binary
